subject: RE: [junit] bat script ends after first ant command
msgSnippet: Try using call ant testClient call ant testJsp call ant testServlet ... From: Alok Daipuria Sent: Thursday, May 01, 2003 8:57 AM To: junit@yahoogroups.com
messageBody:
Try using

call ant testClient
call ant testJsp
call ant testServlet

-----Original Message-----
From: Alok Daipuria
Sent: Thursday, May 01, 2003 8:57 AM
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [junit] bat script ends after first ant command


Hello everyone,
I was running multiple ant commands from a batch file and found that the
bat script doesn't go past the first ant command.
Say your batch file has commands :
ant testClient
ant testJsp
ant testServlet
The bat file will execute only the first one - "ant testClient"

As an alternate, I have to run using the Java command line, which is not
very neat.
Just want to know if anyone faced the problem.

thanks
-alok
